  "body": "Running `teku --help` still shows this, although the default is now tree storage for which this option does not apply:\r\n\r\n```\r\n      --data-storage-archive-frequency=<FREQUENCY>\r\n                             Sets the frequency, in slots, at which to store\r\n                               finalized states to disk. This option is ignored\r\n                               if --data-storage-mode is set to PRUNE\r\n                               Default: 2048\r\n```\r\n\r\nAcceptance criteria:\r\n  1. I don't see this option when running `teku --help`\r\n  1. I _do_ see this option if it is relevant anywhere, for example grouped somewhere with the option to use the old archive storage format, if that's still available.\r\n  1. The [Teku docs](https://docs.teku.consensys.net/en/latest/Reference/CLI/CLI-Syntax/#data-storage-archive-frequency) are updated accordingly.",
